Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.36,0:32:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord. Yeah. Whoever chooses your Lord is\Nyour Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.12,0:33:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's personal. The O Lord\Nexpresses tender, tenderness,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.39,0:33:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,mutual ownership, mutual mutuality.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.20,0:33:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All glory be to thee,\NO Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.91,0:33:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the Lord of all. Then relates to you\Ndirectly
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.39,0:33:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in all the scriptures from no matter\Nwhat the origin says.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.36,0:33:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who\Nturn to me are mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.36,0:33:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you're saying that you are owned\Nby the Lord. When you call the Lord the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.72,0:33:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord, now you're\Ndefining the relationship to divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.08,0:33:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not a me and a God, which is\Nnot any relationship at all. Like me in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.44,0:33:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the wall.\NUnto thee, oh Lord. Unto thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.79,0:34:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Majest is Lord. The Lord cannot refuse\Nyour intreaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.39,0:34:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.\NWhat I just said is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.76,0:34:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Addressed as thee, oh Lord, divinity\Ncannot refuse the infrin the intreaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.32,0:34:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact. Oh Lord. Amen.\NThat is a fact. Oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.04,0:34:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You, oh God, is a separate thing.\NAnd he's not obligated.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.72,0:34:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He gets off the hook.\NHe's like, "And God other than God
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.00,0:34:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,prayers." He sits up there twiddling\Nsome cherubs on his toe.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.67,0:34:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, another old you God prayer\Nto thee, oh Lord. Uh-oh. Now he's got to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.87,0:34:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,put the cherabs down\Nand open himself because
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.76,0:35:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity responds to supplication.\NSo contemplation is a b a contemplative
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.59,0:35:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,lifestyle as I've said before is a very\Nyin way. It's like your life becomes a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.83,0:35:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,mudra by which your supplication\Nthe lord
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.56,0:35:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically responds.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.35,0:35:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> To thee, oh Lord, you don't have to\Nworry if God is listening
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.11,0:35:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to thee, oh Lord.\NGod hears. Resist
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.59,0:35:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to you, oh God.\NGod is not obligated. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.59,0:35:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not obligated. He's not involved.\NYou see, you're talking to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.56,0:36:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling to yourself.\NAll right. So the O Lord indicates
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.48,0:36:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,devotion. Devotion. And all the great\Nthe great Krishna everyone. Those who
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.88,0:36:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,are devoted to me are mine.\NThat's enough to contemplate on for the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.52,0:36:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,next couple years.\NIf you just contemplate that knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.83,0:36:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and just hold it, eventually you reach a\Nstate of extreme joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.35,0:36:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy.\NWhen divinity reveals its essence,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.44,0:36:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,one goes into a state of wonderment\Nwhich is paralyzing wonderment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.35,0:36:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And after you reach that state, you have\Nto stop it or you can't function in the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.96,0:36:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,world.\NBecause as the divinity of all that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.35,0:37:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,exists reveals itself to you, you're\Nstunned and into awe in silent awe and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.35,0:37:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind never says anything again\Non its own. There is no person to think
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.56,0:37:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,having witnessed the reality. Yeah, it's\Nsilenced forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.04,0:37:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So contemplation plus prayer. And you\Nnotice I said supplication,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.92,0:37:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,supplication\Nto thee, oh Lord, do I devote my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.83,0:37:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing beyond that that you as\Na human can say. There's nothing beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.80,0:37:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that. That is the ultimate you can say.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.83,0:37:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the ultimate that can be said\Nresist.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.52,0:37:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I like precision.\NOh god.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.68,0:38:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,With humility goes humor. Goes humor.\NGoes humor. Nobody thinks of humor as a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.20,0:38:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual practice. To me, it's one of\Nthe most powerful ones. There's nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.52,0:38:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the narcissistic ego hates more than\Nbeing laughed at.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.52,0:38:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it was it Nero that declared\Nhimself God. Yeah he declared himself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.59,0:38:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,God. So he must have said to me oh God\Nwe will destroy all of Rome. Uh to me oh
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.59,0:38:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NUh I think humor is one of the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.40,0:38:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,benefits. it be. Why? Because humor is\Nalways contrasting essence with with
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.80,0:38:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,perception.\NIt's always contrasting how the world
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.96,0:38:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,view or you view something and what the\Nreality is. You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.07,0:39:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's the contrast that makes it\Nfunny. It's the contrast that makes it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.96,0:39:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,funny.\NPeople that are very, very serious about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.48,0:39:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,life all the time are dangerous.\NYou never know. Did you ever notice
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.07,0:39:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler laughing?\NStalin joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.40,0:39:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman Mayo.\NPeasants. Peasants. I will lead you to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.96,0:39:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom.\NHow many people died on his great march?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.64,0:39:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The great leader,\Nwhat was it? 30 thou 30,000 died on the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.00,0:39:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,trip\NMayo's great trek across you know I
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.92,0:39:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,think 30,000\NI don't imagine I would call a guy who
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.76,0:39:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would lost 30,000 of his troops just\Ngoing from here to there a great leader
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.44,0:40:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd call him in for a hearing\Nyou lost 30,000 troops from here to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.16,0:40:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Phoenix.\NI don't think I would call him the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.56,0:40:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,great.\NAh, yes. So, humility and humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.24,0:40:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Humor and humility go together. You see\Nwhat I'm saying? When you take yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.72,0:40:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,too seriously, you can be carried away\Nwith yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.28,0:40:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you see how imbecillic you are,\Nmakes you laugh. And then you're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.32,0:40:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,dedication to the path. dedication.\NAlong the pathway, you you become
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.64,0:40:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,increasingly aware of beauty. That first\Nof all, there's the humor. That's the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.04,0:40:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,human perception projected onto life.\NAnd you see the humor of the contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.11,0:40:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,between reality and perception.\NEventually, you become very dedicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.32,0:40:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The pathway or the teachings that I\Nascribe uh is the pathway to God through
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.83,0:41:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute confirmable and verifiable\Ntruth. truth itself. Truth itself is the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.72,0:41:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway to God. Um\Nthere are various ways to the truth of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.72,0:41:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,essence.\NIf you're devoted to integrity and to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.59,0:41:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,honesty and the truth and the perfection\Netc. You become increasingly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.68,0:41:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh sensitive to beauty\Nand the beauty of every of all that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.28,0:41:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,exists.\NBecome increasingly so
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.28,0:41:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I always advise people become aware of\Nthe beauty of each thing. If you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.64,0:41:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,project anything onto it, you see its\Nabsolute perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.44,0:41:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this takes a while for some\Npeople.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.52,0:41:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything\Nis what what it means is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.28,0:42:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything is perfect the way it is.\NIf a shirt is tattered,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.40,0:42:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I like it that way.\NYou reach for your favorite shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.88,0:42:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to the doctor that way.\NYou're not going to the doctor just like
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.59,0:42:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\NAll right. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.76,0:42:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,she sees beauty uh in beauty. And I see\Nbeauty in in torn old shirts.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.64,0:42:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's actually not beauty. It's\Nattachment. Attachment to a nice old
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.56,0:43:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,shirt.\NBut you see that it's a perfect old
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.16,0:43:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,shirt. You understand?\Nshirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.35,0:43:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> A perfect old shirt. I mean, it's a\Nperfect raggedy old shirt. A nice new
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.80,0:43:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,crispy shirt. Isn't like a nice raggedy\Nold one that's been washed 50 times. You
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.96,0:43:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,know that yourself.\NIsn't that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.16,0:43:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You note the perfection of everything.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.96,0:43:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what I've all, you know, emphasized\Nalmost every lecture is to get beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.96,0:43:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the delusion of cause and effect. That's\Na hard one for modern man to get you in
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.04,0:43:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a scientific world to stop seeing things\Nin terms of cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.64,0:43:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What what happens is certain conditions\Nincrease likelihoods, but they don't
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.59,0:43:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,cause them. Nothing causes.\NNothing causes anything. Nothing has a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.59,0:44:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cause. Everything has a source and an\Norigin. The s the source in of the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.48,0:44:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,universe is divinity.\Nout of the godhead
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.35,0:44:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear godhead. The godhead doesn't\Ndo anything. Doesn't even create
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.64,0:44:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,universes.\NOut of the godhead emerges the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.83,0:44:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality\Nof divinity as creator. The creator then
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.92,0:44:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes the source which is present\Ncontinuously at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.24,0:44:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the infinite power of the source,\Nall existence source
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.48,0:44:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality\Nactualizes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.31,0:44:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as an actuality.\NNow because the power of the presence is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.52,0:44:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so powerful,\Npotentiality actualizes because of the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.59,0:44:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,power of the consciousness of divinity\Nas the constant source.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.28,0:45:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you have to be get beyond the\Nidea of a linear universe in which there
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.24,0:45:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was before time then suddenly God\Nemerged created a linear universe that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.40,0:45:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,starts there stops here and then God\Nexits. I mean that's a juvenile
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.07,0:45:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,grade school concept.\NIt's because it's seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.31,0:45:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,reality as linear whereas reality is\Nnonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.07,0:45:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite potentiality exists beyond\Nall time. It has no beginning. There is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.88,0:45:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,no first cause. Nor does it have an end.\NYeah. It's not possible for that which
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.04,0:45:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is alwaysness and foreverness to have a\Nbeginning or an end. And I realized that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.92,0:45:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially\Nat age 12 or 14 or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.00,0:45:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I experienced it before that too. but\Nvery vividly
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.04,0:46:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as a young teenager when time came to a\Nstop and an infinite presence beyond all
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.28,0:46:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,description\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.72,0:46:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,prevailed\Nand the knowingness was that that which
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.11,0:46:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I am existed before all universes and\Nwill exist after all universes have
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.31,0:46:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,disappeared.\NThat which I am is beyond time, beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.96,0:46:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,causation\Nis not different than infinite love and
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.04,0:46:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite power.\NAnd the infinite power of infinite love
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.20,0:46:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is strange because like that which is\Nthe most gentle, exquisitly gentleness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.07,0:46:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that melts you, it is simultaneously\Ninfinitely powerful and cannot be
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.20,0:46:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,resisted.\NThat which is infinitely soft and
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.40,0:46:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite is simultaneously more\Npowerful than steel. There is no way you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.11,0:46:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can alter it in the slightest. No power\Npower on earth because it is infinitely
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.56,0:47:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful. Uh\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.07,0:47:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you note the perfection and the beauty\Nof all things and then you begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.68,0:47:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,notice that each thing is occurring as\Nan actualization of a potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.40,0:47:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's no cause for anything. So\Nonce you get beyond cause the world your
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.68,0:47:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of the world becomes\Ntransformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.59,0:47:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual practices in daily life\Nare assisted by certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.07,0:47:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the practice and certain things\Nget in your way. So we wanted to list
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.07,0:47:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that we should let go of and\Nthe things that we should accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.76,0:47:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To let go of what I've just spoken about\Nis the idea that there is a cause for
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.88,0:47:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. There is that which is\Nantecedent and then there is that which
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.31,0:48:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is subsequent. But cause is a magical\Nnotion of the mind and it's projected
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.48,0:48:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,into the world. You cannot find cause\Nanywhere in the world. You can only find
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.72,0:48:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,sequence.\NYou cannot find any cause there any
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.11,0:48:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,cause there. That's a mental projection.\NAll right. Um, so you have to be willing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.59,0:48:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender\Nthe negatives. So we sort of started at
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.52,0:48:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom of the the scale of\Nconsciousness. You have to be willing to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.20,0:48:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender\Nuh hatred. And how do you do that? By
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.59,0:48:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,humility, you surrender to God's will.\NHow can you what can you say? Why why
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.20,0:48:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,would people hang on to hatred? Because\Nhatred
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.07,0:48:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh pumps up the egotism, the egotism of\Nthe narcissistic core, the ego. Because
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.76,0:48:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,people enjoy hate, people love to hate.\NYou can see every night on television,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.55,0:49:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,big demonstration, some capital of the\Nworld, throwing rocks, bottles, killing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.31,0:49:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,police, setting fires, looting, etc.\NPeople love hate. Just try and take hate
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.83,0:49:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,away from them. Oh boy, you're gonna\Nhave a hard time. Most dangerous thing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.76,0:49:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is to try and take hate away from\Npeople. They'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.20,0:49:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They will.\NThey love to hate. And the only way you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.48,0:49:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,can hate is to blacken something and\Nvilify it. So to get them off hate, you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.31,0:49:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,would have to they would have to stop\Nvilifying, which again is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.04,0:49:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because the ego gets such a charge,\Nexcitement, and so much energy out of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.76,0:49:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred. It loves hatred. It loves war.\NIt loves killing. Loves murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.48,0:49:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,stabbing, suicide, shooting.\NIt loves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.52,0:50:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It loves it. Once you see that people\Nlove it, then it sort of changes how you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.24,0:50:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you you view them. It's an addiction.\NThey're hooked on hate. Hooked on hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.44,0:50:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're always looking for something\Nnew to hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.28,0:50:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the blogger blogger land is full of\Nuh something good comes up. The minute
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.11,0:50:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,something is labeled as good, the haters\Ncome up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.44,0:50:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's bad to label anything as good. Do\Nnot label anything as good.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.20,0:50:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody hates good. Everybody hates\Nsuccessful.
