Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.11,1:05:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh one of the karmic consequences,\Nkarmic consequences is that we are as
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.40,1:05:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,humans stuck with the ego and the\Nproblems that automatically go with
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.31,1:05:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,having an ego. So we could get a\Nresentment about that except we say well
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.92,1:05:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the price of the gift of life\Nitself. I would rather be alive and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.35,1:05:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,working on the inherent problems\Nintrinsic to being human uh than dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.16,1:05:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be thankful for life to see the\Nworld as an evolving creation and to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.52,1:05:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,accept that your time here is limited.\NYou accept the earlier in life you pick
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.48,1:05:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you you accept mortality the better\Nbecause of all the psychological fears
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.72,1:06:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom of all the piles is the\Nfear of death itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.59,1:06:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get over that one nobody\Ncan really do anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.59,1:06:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I know guy says I'm going to kill you.\NWell it's your problem buddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.07,1:06:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his problem. It's his goddamn\Nproblem. If he wants to kill me,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.35,1:06:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not my problem. It's his problem.\NSo, he gets that that you picture it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.48,1:06:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's his problem and you can walk\Nright through the all kinds of stuff and
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.59,1:06:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told you some of the things I've\Nwalked through to completely unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.52,1:06:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You pull the trigger, it's your problem.\NI don't give a damn, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.16,1:06:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but you got to mean that. I wouldn't try\Nit if you didn't mean it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.64,1:06:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll say, "Oh, yeah. Let's see."\NBoing. Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.48,1:06:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsic and and hidden beneath is is\Nthe exquisite beauty and perfection of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.28,1:06:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,God's love, which expresses itself as\Nmercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.52,1:07:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which is merciful is probably\Nthe mercifulness of all of life is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.52,1:07:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,probably the most difficult of all\Nthings to see. The beauty of life you
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.24,1:07:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually see. The reflection of all of\Nlife you eventually see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.07,1:07:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But the mercy of all of life, that's the\Nhard one to see. That intrinsic to what
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.48,1:07:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you see is disaster\Nis divine mercy. Allowing that you the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.72,1:07:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,grace of undoing that negative karma\Nwhich would would have put you into hell
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.07,1:07:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have now undone it. Thank you,\Noh Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.16,1:07:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for my salvation. Yeah,\Nthrough human life, we reach salvation
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.24,1:07:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,through the undoing of negative karma,\Nthe adoption of positive karma. That's
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.59,1:07:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,one way of putting it. And therefore,\Nhuman life is an expression of divine
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.00,1:08:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,grace and infinite mercy.\NSo, we'll take a break there.
